Feature: Updating FIU branding configuration

  Scenario: Successfully updating branding configuration
    Given the API endpoint for updating FIU branding configuration exists
    And the request payload contains valid branding configuration data
    When a POST request is sent to the endpoint
    Then the response status code should be 200
    And the response should contain a success message or indication of successful update

  Scenario: Handling missing or invalid payload
    Given the API endpoint for updating FIU branding configuration exists
    And the request payload is missing or invalid
    When a POST request is sent to the endpoint
    Then the response status code should be 400 or appropriate indicating bad request
    And the response body should contain an error message indicating missing or invalid payload

  Scenario: Handling unauthorized access
    Given the API endpoint for updating FIU branding configuration exists
    And the request is sent without proper authentication or authorization credentials
    When a POST request is sent to the endpoint
    Then the response status code should be 401 or 403 indicating unauthorized access

  Scenario: Handling endpoint not found
    When a POST request is sent to a non-existent endpoint
    Then the response status code should be 404 or appropriate indicating endpoint not found

  Scenario: Handling invalid request method
    Given the API endpoint for updating FIU branding configuration exists
    When a request other than POST method is sent to the endpoint (e.g., GET, PUT, DELETE)
    Then the response status code should be 405 indicating method not allowed

  Scenario: Handling internal server error
